      • hammingMethodDistance

        public static int hammingMethodDistance(java.io.File file1,
                                        java.io.File file2)
                                 throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        This method uses a way to compute the Hamming distance not on every character of two strings but on every line of two files. In this way we can compute the distance between the methods of two different chains in a way that is the same used in the Hamming distance.
        Parameters:
        file1 - The first file containing the first chain of methods.
        file2 - The second file containing the second chain of methods.
        Returns:
        An integer representing the distance between the two chains.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - When a file doesn't exists

      • levenshteinMethodDistance

        public static int levenshteinMethodDistance(java.io.File file1,
                                            java.io.File file2)
                                     throws java.io.FileNotFoundException
        This method uses a way to compute the Levenshtein distance not on every character of two strings but on every line of two files. In this way we can compute the distance between the methods of two different chains in a way that is the same used in the Levenshtein distance. This is the best way to calculate the different methods in two chains that have not the same length.
        Parameters:
        file1 - The first file containing the first chain of methods.
        file2 - The second file containing the second chain of methods.
        Returns:
        An integer representing the distance between the two chains.
        Throws:
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - When a file doesn't exists
